This month I’ve been watching One Day at a time season 3 and Cloak…

summary: Too Good at Goodbyes (mczuckles)
body:
Too Good at Goodbyes (mczuckles)

Copied from my wattpad like usual, written like a week or two ago lmao

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Everytime you hurt me, the less that I cry. And every time you leave me, the quicker these tears dry. Every time you walk out the less I love you.

“Fine! Fucking leave! You always do!”

“That’s unfair Mace! You-”

“NO! You wanna know what’s unfair?! That you keep fucking doing this to me! If you don’t love me, you could just say! Instead you’ve repeatedly hurt me, and you know that it stings!”

Mason broke down then, curling his shaking limbs around each other. He spoke through tears “please just go.” His eyes were pleading, and admittedly, that’s why the older listened.

Jay slowly walked out the door, sending one last look the other’s way. It was genuine, real, and meaningful. But it only made official what they knew to be true.

He would never come back.

Baby we don’t stand a chance, it’s sad but it’s true.
